00:02:49.630 --> 00:02:55.890
Human brain is an amazing thing.

00:02:55.890 --> 00:02:57.890
The inventions we brought into this world.

00:02:57.890 --> 00:03:02.890
Imagine, 3 billion years of evolution to create this.

00:03:02.890 --> 00:03:04.890
Hey, over here.

00:03:04.890 --> 00:03:06.890
Mind boggles when you think about evolution.

00:03:06.890 --> 00:03:09.890
Especially when you realize our prehistoric ancestors couldn't think at all.

00:03:09.890 --> 00:03:11.890
Not with brains about as big as a plonk.

00:03:11.890 --> 00:03:13.890
Hey, toss it back, will ya?

00:03:13.890 --> 00:03:14.890
They crawled, ate roots and bark.

00:03:14.890 --> 00:03:16.890
No one owned Frisbees.

00:03:17.890 --> 00:03:19.890
The first giant leap was called Homo Havilus.

00:03:19.890 --> 00:03:22.890
Havilus created tools to hunt and dig.

00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:25.890
He wasn't really human, but at least he was smarter than a plum.

00:03:26.890 --> 00:03:29.890
The next stage in development was Homo erectus.

00:03:29.890 --> 00:03:31.890
Erectus discovered fire.

00:03:31.890 --> 00:03:34.890
Okay, so it wasn't the microwave, but at least you could cook your food.

00:03:34.890 --> 00:03:38.890
Maybe erectus had a bigger brain, but he still smelled worse than a goat.

00:03:39.890 --> 00:03:42.890
Then came Homo sapiens, modern humans, us.

00:03:42.890 --> 00:03:46.890
Homo sapiens discovered speech so we could give voice to our minds and express our emotions.

00:03:47.890 --> 00:03:50.890
What?

00:03:50.890 --> 00:03:52.890
Parsnip.

00:03:52.890 --> 00:03:56.890
Of course, some quarters have more on their minds than others.

00:03:56.890 --> 00:03:58.890
Could you throw back the Frisbee already?

00:03:58.890 --> 00:04:01.890
Okay, I'll admit, learning to speak was a big development.

00:04:01.890 --> 00:04:03.890
But I'd trade all of our finest achievements.

00:04:03.890 --> 00:04:06.890
The automatic teller machine, the five-speed transmission,

00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:08.890
and chocolate chip milkshakes.

00:04:08.890 --> 00:04:10.890
To never hear Ferguson speak again.

00:04:10.890 --> 00:04:12.890
I wonder, could I stand the peace?

00:04:12.890 --> 00:04:15.890
Thanks for nothing, barf face.

00:04:15.890 --> 00:04:19.300
Or be that lucky.

00:04:19.300 --> 00:05:20.370
59 cents.

00:05:20.370 --> 00:05:24.510
Whoa, what am I doing?

00:05:24.510 --> 00:05:27.510
Who cares about a coupon for canned carrots?

00:05:27.510 --> 00:05:30.510
I hate canned carrots, and I hate clipping coupons.

00:05:30.510 --> 00:05:32.510
It's a dangerous business.

00:05:32.510 --> 00:05:35.510
What looks like a great deal in the newspaper is no bargain on a dinner plate.

00:05:35.510 --> 00:05:38.510
Of course, I wouldn't be here at all except for this guy.

00:05:38.510 --> 00:05:42.510
Fish face Eddie, the biggest gangster in the state, and my mom's on the jury.

00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:47.510
The papers are full of stuff about the trial, so that's why she's not allowed to read the paper.

00:05:47.510 --> 00:05:50.510
So who gets stuck doing coupons?

00:05:50.510 --> 00:05:54.510
And that, ladies and gentlemen of the jury, is the real human tragedy of organized crime.

00:05:54.510 --> 00:05:56.510
Don't want the paper yet?

00:05:56.510 --> 00:05:59.510
Why, did you mess all over the carpet again? Bad job, bad job!

00:05:59.510 --> 00:06:02.510
Oh, you are in rare form today. You mind hurrying up?

00:06:02.510 --> 00:06:04.510
You mind stuffing the sofa in your mouth?

00:06:04.510 --> 00:06:06.510
Okay, you just call me when you're done with the paper.

00:06:06.510 --> 00:06:09.510
Or if you need any help with the big words.

00:06:09.510 --> 00:06:11.510
Wait, what does this word mean?

00:06:11.510 --> 00:06:13.510
Fratricide.

00:06:13.510 --> 00:06:16.510
Oh, that means killing your brother.

00:06:16.510 --> 00:06:18.510
Very funny.

00:06:18.510 --> 00:06:20.510
Of course, there is a brighter side to clipping coupons.

00:06:20.510 --> 00:06:22.510
You control what the family eats.

00:06:22.510 --> 00:06:24.510
And you learn how coupons save money.

00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:31.510
For instance, this is the saving on low-fat yogurt, celery, and calcium and rich OJ.

00:06:31.510 --> 00:06:34.510
Now here's what you save on candy.

00:06:34.510 --> 00:06:35.510
Broke punch.

00:06:35.510 --> 00:06:37.510
And single serving strawberry cheesecake.

00:06:37.510 --> 00:06:38.510
Huge.

00:06:38.510 --> 00:06:40.510
Sure the junk food costs more to start.

00:06:40.510 --> 00:06:42.510
Makes you fat and rots your teeth.

00:06:42.510 --> 00:06:43.510
But hey, look at the savings.

00:06:43.510 --> 00:06:44.510
Won't mom be proud?

00:06:44.510 --> 00:06:46.510
What is taking you so long?

00:06:46.510 --> 00:06:47.510
It was such a lovely family.

00:06:47.510 --> 00:06:49.510
A father, a mother, a daughter.

00:06:49.510 --> 00:06:51.510
When out of the news came something so vile.

00:06:51.510 --> 00:06:53.510
Look, enough. I just want the paper.

00:06:53.510 --> 00:06:55.510
And still he speaks.

00:06:55.510 --> 00:06:56.510
Well, I'll tell you, Bergberg,

00:06:56.510 --> 00:06:58.510
I got distracted by this letter to the editor.

00:06:58.510 --> 00:07:01.510
It's from your real parents on Mars.

00:07:01.510 --> 00:07:03.510
It says here they refuse to take you back

00:07:03.510 --> 00:07:05.510
because they know how unpopular you are on earth.

00:07:05.510 --> 00:07:07.510
Uh-huh, real funny. You know, you can just...

00:07:07.510 --> 00:07:09.510
You're a...

00:07:09.510 --> 00:07:12.790
Give me your best shot.

00:07:12.790 --> 00:07:14.790
You'd like that, wouldn't you?

00:07:14.790 --> 00:07:16.790
So you can insult me again.

00:07:16.790 --> 00:07:18.790
Well, maybe for once

00:07:18.790 --> 00:07:21.790
I won't give you that satisfaction.

00:07:21.790 --> 00:07:23.790
You mean you're speechless?

00:07:23.790 --> 00:07:25.790
I can't believe it. My prayers are answered.

00:07:25.790 --> 00:07:28.790
Until you apologize for your constant insults,

00:07:28.790 --> 00:07:30.790
I'm staying silent.

00:07:30.790 --> 00:07:32.790
Finally, peace and quiet.

00:07:32.790 --> 00:07:34.790
Quiet? Maybe. Peace.

00:07:34.790 --> 00:07:36.790
I think not.

00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:38.790
Ferguson thinks not.

00:07:38.790 --> 00:07:40.790
True words were never spoken.

00:07:40.790 --> 00:07:50.130
Are you just gonna sit there saying nothing?

00:07:50.130 --> 00:07:54.890
Are you trying to drive me crazy?

00:07:57.890 --> 00:08:00.890
Did you know that sometimes crazy people commit murder?

00:08:00.890 --> 00:08:07.060
Hey, guys. Is Mom home yet?

00:08:07.060 --> 00:08:09.060
Not yet, Dad.

00:08:09.060 --> 00:08:11.060
Dad, let's say you wanted to kill your brother.

00:08:11.060 --> 00:08:13.060
Would you get a chair or a medal?

00:08:13.060 --> 00:08:16.060
Ferguson, isn't one trial of this family enough?

00:08:16.060 --> 00:08:18.060
Look at him, Dad.

00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:20.060
How he just sits there.

00:08:20.060 --> 00:08:23.060
He's doing nothing. That's annoying you?

00:08:23.060 --> 00:08:25.060
He's doing nothing on purpose.

00:08:25.060 --> 00:08:28.060
Well, Clarissa, that is hardly a capital offense.

00:08:28.060 --> 00:08:30.060
Dad, he won't stop.

00:08:30.060 --> 00:08:33.060
Well, I don't know how to stop nothing.

00:08:33.060 --> 00:08:35.060
Wait a minute.

00:08:35.060 --> 00:08:37.060
Is this the silent treatment?

00:08:37.060 --> 00:08:39.060
It's a silent treatment, all right.

00:08:39.060 --> 00:08:41.060
Well, it's a classic,

00:08:41.060 --> 00:08:44.060
and I gotta tell you, sport, it's almost impossible to beat.

00:08:44.060 --> 00:08:46.060
I don't know what you did,

00:08:46.060 --> 00:08:48.060
but just go ahead and apologize before it really gets to you.

00:08:48.060 --> 00:08:50.060
Wait, you think I can't get him to break down?

00:08:50.060 --> 00:08:52.060
Well, I've never seen it happen,

00:08:52.060 --> 00:08:55.060
except for that one time with the Cracker Derby brothers.

00:08:55.060 --> 00:08:56.060
Who were they?

00:08:56.060 --> 00:08:59.060
Well, I grew up with these guys, Jim and Jeff Cracker Derby.

00:08:59.060 --> 00:09:01.060
Jim didn't talk to his brother for four and a half years

00:09:01.060 --> 00:09:03.060
until he finally spoke.

00:09:03.060 --> 00:09:04.060
What happened?

00:09:04.060 --> 00:09:05.060
Well, he finally yelled,

00:09:05.060 --> 00:09:06.060
Watch out!

00:09:06.060 --> 00:09:08.060
Just as Jeff got hit by the bus.

00:09:08.060 --> 00:09:10.060
Hello. Hello, everybody.

00:09:10.060 --> 00:09:12.060
Hey, look who's here.

00:09:12.060 --> 00:09:13.060
How'd it go, hon?

00:09:13.060 --> 00:09:16.060
Now you know the rules. No talking about the case.

00:09:16.060 --> 00:09:18.060
How can you sit on the jury that is trying

00:09:18.060 --> 00:09:20.060
to fish-face Eddie and not talk about it,

00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:21.060
especially the way they caught him.

00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:23.060
The surveillance, the wiretap.

00:09:23.060 --> 00:09:24.060
Yeah, the paper says it's the jury.

00:09:24.060 --> 00:09:26.060
Now both of you stop.

00:09:26.060 --> 00:09:28.060
Oh, come on. We won't tell anybody.

00:09:28.060 --> 00:09:29.060
No.

00:09:29.060 --> 00:09:31.060
Mom, you're acting like your own house's bug.

00:09:31.060 --> 00:09:33.060
Don't be silly. They wouldn't do that.

00:09:33.060 --> 00:09:37.060
I mean, they do have all our names in the brasses, Merton.

00:09:37.060 --> 00:09:41.060
Testing one, two, three.

00:09:41.060 --> 00:09:43.060
Ferguson, you haven't said a word. Are you all right?

00:09:43.060 --> 00:09:44.060
Well, this island tree.

00:09:44.060 --> 00:09:46.060
Oh, with who? Clarissa?

00:09:46.060 --> 00:09:47.060
Yeah.

00:09:47.060 --> 00:09:49.060
Oh, well, good luck, dear.

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:51.060
Clarissa, strawberry cheesecakes.

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:53.060
There's no way I'm buying that.

00:09:55.060 --> 00:09:57.430
Shut up.

00:09:57.430 --> 00:10:04.300
What can make Ferguson break his silence?

00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:06.300
Well, that could break his neck.

00:10:06.300 --> 00:10:08.300
It's one of the 47 different body parts that I've discovered

00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:12.300
when bent just so is guaranteed to produce at least an ouch.

00:10:12.300 --> 00:10:14.300
But pain as a solution?

00:10:14.300 --> 00:10:15.300
I don't know.

00:10:15.300 --> 00:10:17.300
I need a plan. I need inspiration.

00:10:17.300 --> 00:10:20.610
I need help.

00:10:20.610 --> 00:10:22.610
Hi, Sam.

00:10:22.610 --> 00:10:24.610
You're just the man I want to see.

00:10:24.610 --> 00:10:25.610
What's up?

00:10:25.610 --> 00:10:27.610
If you wanted to do something really awful to someone

00:10:27.610 --> 00:10:30.610
guaranteed to make him scream at you, what would you do?

00:10:30.610 --> 00:10:32.610
That's easy. I'd ask you.

00:10:32.610 --> 00:10:33.610
Come on, Sam.

00:10:33.610 --> 00:10:35.610
Fergface won't fight with me, and it's driving me nuts.

00:10:35.610 --> 00:10:38.610
Wait a minute. I thought you hate fighting with him.

00:10:38.610 --> 00:10:41.610
Do you see? He is fighting by not fighting.

00:10:41.610 --> 00:10:43.610
It's the ultimate battle between us.

00:10:43.610 --> 00:10:44.610
Worse than any fight before.

00:10:44.610 --> 00:10:48.610
He's torturing me, and he's using the silent treatment.

00:10:48.610 --> 00:10:50.610
Oh, quit now. Just do whatever he wants.

00:10:50.610 --> 00:10:52.610
Apologize and get it over with.

00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:53.610
No way.

00:10:53.610 --> 00:10:56.610
Now, so far, I've come up with tie-dying all of his underwear,

00:10:56.610 --> 00:10:58.610
but that's out because I'd actually have to touch his underwear.

00:10:58.610 --> 00:11:00.610
Anything else?

00:11:00.610 --> 00:11:02.610
Well, I could mix shampoo with his mashed potatoes,

00:11:02.610 --> 00:11:04.610
but Y-Way's perfectly good shampoo.

00:11:04.610 --> 00:11:06.610
Well, there's something he used to do,

00:11:06.610 --> 00:11:08.610
and scouts that got people pretty mad.

00:11:08.610 --> 00:11:10.610
You wait until the guy's asleep,

00:11:10.610 --> 00:11:13.610
and then you spread peanut butter in between his toes.

00:11:13.610 --> 00:11:15.610
I don't know. Seems pretty juvenile.

00:11:15.610 --> 00:11:16.610
Chunky your plane.

00:11:16.610 --> 00:11:19.610
How far apart are his toes?

00:11:19.610 --> 00:11:21.610
I'd stick to the plane.

00:11:21.610 --> 00:11:24.610
Tell me, Sam, is this what you guys learn in scouts?

00:11:24.610 --> 00:11:26.610
Well, they try to teach you the basics,

00:11:26.610 --> 00:11:28.610
so you grew up right.

00:11:28.610 --> 00:11:31.610
I'll try it, but somehow I think I'm going to need something more.

00:11:31.610 --> 00:11:32.610
Really?

00:11:32.610 --> 00:11:35.610
This is no human child we're talking about.

00:11:35.610 --> 00:11:37.610
This is Ferguson.

00:11:37.610 --> 00:11:52.300
You just going into the kitchen?

00:11:52.300 --> 00:11:53.300
Yeah. Oh.

00:11:53.300 --> 00:11:54.300
Is everything all right?

00:11:54.300 --> 00:11:56.300
Oh, well, it's probably nothing to worry about,

00:11:56.300 --> 00:11:59.300
but there was a little problem with the refrigerator,

00:11:59.300 --> 00:12:01.300
so Stewie Stoutenheimer sent over a repairman.

00:12:01.300 --> 00:12:02.300
Yeah.

00:12:02.300 --> 00:12:04.300
Well, it was a new guy.

00:12:04.300 --> 00:12:05.300
Yeah?

00:12:05.300 --> 00:12:08.300
Well, how do I know if it was really one of Stewie's men?

00:12:08.300 --> 00:12:10.300
It could have been, you know,

00:12:10.300 --> 00:12:13.300
somebody working for the government or a fish-face eddy.

00:12:13.300 --> 00:12:18.300
Janet, are you getting a little caught up in this trial?

00:12:18.300 --> 00:12:22.300
Marshall, if you only knew how they planted that bog on fish-fish,

00:12:22.300 --> 00:12:24.300
you would...

00:12:24.300 --> 00:12:26.300
Let's just say I had no idea

00:12:26.300 --> 00:12:28.300
what they could do with high-tech electronics

00:12:28.300 --> 00:12:30.300
and a bowl of stuffed olives.

00:12:30.300 --> 00:12:32.300
So you want me to...

00:12:32.300 --> 00:12:34.300
Just check the fridge for anything out of the ordinary.

00:12:34.300 --> 00:12:36.300
You know, like a microphone or something.

00:12:36.300 --> 00:12:37.300
A microphone?

00:12:37.300 --> 00:12:39.300
Shh, not so loud.

00:12:39.300 --> 00:12:40.300
The cops could be listening.

00:12:40.300 --> 00:12:42.300
I want a fish-face as good.

00:12:42.300 --> 00:12:44.300
Excuse me. Can I get through?

00:12:44.300 --> 00:12:48.290
Everybody okay?

00:12:48.290 --> 00:12:50.290
Yeah.

00:12:50.290 --> 00:12:53.290
Oh, and Marshall, could you take these coupons in?

00:12:53.290 --> 00:12:55.290
I mean, since you're going in anyway.

00:12:55.290 --> 00:12:57.290
Oh, sure, that's no problem.

00:12:57.290 --> 00:12:58.290
Thanks, dear.

00:12:58.290 --> 00:13:06.460
Hey, Sport, what's up?

00:13:06.460 --> 00:13:09.460
Tell me, Dad, what is it about little brothers?

00:13:09.460 --> 00:13:12.460
Well, you'll have to give me more to go on, Sport.

00:13:12.460 --> 00:13:14.460
Those are some magazines they get with instructions

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:16.460
on how to bother everyone.

00:13:16.460 --> 00:13:18.460
Or is there some special skills class at school

00:13:18.460 --> 00:13:19.460
that girls don't know about

00:13:19.460 --> 00:13:21.460
where brothers learn their annoying little habits?

00:13:21.460 --> 00:13:23.460
Yeah, what habits are those?

00:13:23.460 --> 00:13:25.460
You know, little things like

00:13:25.460 --> 00:13:27.460
opening their eyes in the morning,

00:13:27.460 --> 00:13:29.460
yawning, breathing.

00:13:29.460 --> 00:13:31.460
Is there some sixth sense they possess

00:13:31.460 --> 00:13:33.460
which tells them to eat all the peanut butter

00:13:33.460 --> 00:13:35.460
just when you've come up with a perfectly amazing use for it?

00:13:35.460 --> 00:13:37.460
Oh, boy, Sport, I have never seen

00:13:37.460 --> 00:13:39.460
the silent treatment work this fast.

00:13:39.460 --> 00:13:41.460
I'm telling you, give it up.

00:13:41.460 --> 00:13:42.460
Save yourself the frustration

00:13:42.460 --> 00:13:44.460
and live to fight another day.

00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:46.460
No way. I'm just warming up.

00:13:46.460 --> 00:13:48.460
Sport, I know this sounds crazy,

00:13:48.460 --> 00:13:50.460
but have you noticed anything strange about the fridge

00:13:50.460 --> 00:13:52.460
or, you know, what's in it?

00:13:52.460 --> 00:13:54.460
It's all pretty strange, Dad.

00:13:54.460 --> 00:13:56.460
Haven't you noticed?

00:13:56.460 --> 00:13:58.460
Mom does most of the cooking.

00:13:58.460 --> 00:14:03.950
I just don't know what it is about Ferguson

00:14:03.950 --> 00:14:05.950
that keeps us locked in this constant, tragic conflict.

00:14:05.950 --> 00:14:07.950
He's like this inflamed tonsil

00:14:07.950 --> 00:14:09.950
that just grinds and grinds at you.

00:14:09.950 --> 00:14:11.950
Except, of course, tonsils can be removed.

00:14:11.950 --> 00:14:13.950
No, it's more like when you bash your big toe

00:14:13.950 --> 00:14:15.950
on a table leg.

00:14:15.950 --> 00:14:17.950
Every time you think it's finally healed,

00:14:17.950 --> 00:14:19.950
